div1.p: In the Circuit Court of the United States for the District of Washington, Northern Division:
Ex parte M. L. Coovert. } Petition for Habeas Corpus. Return to the Writ.

To the Circuit Court of the United States for the District of Washington: George Nerton, Sheriff of Clarke County, State of Washington, to whom the within writ is directed, has now and here before the court the body of M. L. Coovert, therein names as thereby commanded. And I the said George Nerton do hereby certify that the cause of the arrest and detention of said M. L. Coovert is a Warrant of Commitment to me directed, issued by the Honorable E. A. Wiswall, Judge of the Superior Court for the State of Washington in the County of Clarke, sitting as committing magistrate, a copy of which Warrant of Commitment is hereto annexed, marked Exhibit No. 1, and made a part hereof, which said warrant was issued in the manner and under the facts and circumstances and for the purpose set forth in the petition of the said M. L. Coovert herein.
Geo. Nerton Sheriff of Clarke County, State of Washington.
